  "editorial": {
    "headline": "Meckler's Single Lifts Angels Past Orioles in Ten Innings",
    "subheadline": "Dramatic Finish in the 10th Innings Lifts Los Angeles Angels",
    "lead_angle": "Wade Meckler lined a single into the outfield grass, scoring two runs in the bottom of the tenth inning to deliver the Los Angeles Angels a 7-6 victory over the visiting Baltimore Orioles. Meckler’s clutch hit against a drawn-in infield capped a back-and-forth contest at Angel Stadium. The hit made a winner of Chase Silseth and sent a stunned Baltimore squad back to the dugout with Keegan Akin tagged for the loss. It was a sudden, sharp end to a long night.\n\nBaltimore carried a three-run cushion into the eighth, looking poised to salt the game away. But the Angels’ bats woke up just in time. Jorge Soler ignited the rally with a towering two-run home run, slicing the deficit to one. Los Angeles manufactured another run before the inning was through, tying the game at five and wiping out the lead the Orioles had held since the third frame. That late surge forced extra innings and set the stage for Meckler’s heroics.\n\nThe loss spoiled a titanic night from Orioles catcher Samuel Basallo. He accounted for most of his team's offense, going 2-for-5 with two home runs and four runs batted in. His three-run blast in the third inning staked Baltimore to an early advantage that their pitching couldn't protect. For the Orioles, it was a frustrating collapse on the road, wasting a powerful offensive display from their backstop and losing ground in a tight pennant race.",
    "reason": "Extra-inning walk-off — the purest combination of tension and resolution the sport offers."
  },
